      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening) must be justified relative to the physical deformation mechanisms observed in testing; alternative model forms must be considered.",
      "rationale": "A bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model for Ti-6Al-4V ELI was selected based on published monotonic tensile coupon data and is consistent with the predominantly monotonic loading in F1717. An elastic-only alternative was evaluated and rejected because it over-predicts yield force by >15%. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions must be sourced from measured lot-specific data with uncertainty quantified; sensitivity analysis must identify dominant inputs.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E = 113.8 ± 2.1 GPa, σ_y = 880 ± 12 MPa) were measured from the same Ti-6Al-4V ELI bar stock used to manufacture the test constructs. Geometric dimensions were taken from CMM measurements of three representative screws. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis identified elastic modulus and yield strength as dominant; their combined uncertainty contribution to stiffness QoI is 3.1%. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test constructs must be production-representative; sample size must provide statistical power ≥0.8 for the primary QoI at the specified acceptance bound.",
      "rationale": "All N=11 constructs were assembled from production-lot screws, rods, and connectors by the device manufacturer. Sample size analysis confirmed power = 0.83 for detecting a 10% mean difference in stiffness at α = 0.05. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate the ASTM F1717 protocol and must span at least two clinically relevant loading magnitudes to assess linearity of construct response.",
      "rationale": "Testing strictly followed ASTM F1717 at a single load level (up to 40 mm displacement). A second loading condition was not included due to resource constraints. This limits the ability to assess construct response linearity and represents a gap relative to the required level 3. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3; this shortfall is documented and accepted based on the overall credibility margin across the remaining factors."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions) must be demonstrably equivalent to the physical test configuration; any deviations must be quantified and shown to have negligible effect on QoI.",
      "rationale": "Model geometry was derived from CAD files verified against CMM measurements (max deviation 0.03 mm). Boundary conditions replicate the F1717 fixture geometry. Friction coefficient at the fixture interface was measured (μ = 0.18) and confirmed by sensitivity analysis to contribute <1% to stiffness QoI. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI comparison must use a statistically rigorous metric (E/uval) with pre-specified acceptance bound; results must be presented with experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) were compared using the E/uval metric per ASME V&V 40 Section 9. Pre-specified acceptance bound E/uval < 1.96 was met for all QoIs (1.31, 1.54, 1.72). Experimental uncertainty was quantified from inter-laboratory reproducibility data. Achieved level 4 exceeds required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
