      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The selected QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) must be directly linked to the clinical risk endpoints identified in the risk assessment.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness is linked to adjacent segment disease risk; yield force and force at 40 mm are linked to construct fracture and revision surgery risk. The traceability from QoI to clinical risk endpoint is documented in the device risk file. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
