      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation scenario (F1717 bench test) must be demonstrated to be representative of the COU (clinical compression-bending loading of the implanted construct).",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 is the FDA-recognized consensus standard for spinal implant compression-bending characterization and is accepted as representative of worst-case clinical loading for regulatory submissions. The bench test geometry replicates the L4-L5 two-level construct configuration specified in the COU. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
